laboratory_examinations.findings: Diffuse dropout of liver signal on out of phase images compatible with hepatic steatosis (Fat fraction is 2%). Millimetric mildly T2 hyperintense lesion in segment 7 likely a hemangioma. Intra and extrahepatic bile ducts normal caliber. Small gallstone in gallbladder with small amount of pericholecystic fluid. Pancreas demonstrates homogeneous signal; pancreatic duct not dilated. Normal spleen size. Right adrenal gland unremarkable; 0.6 cm nodular thickening of the left adrenal gland likely benign. Millimetric T2 hyperintense lesion in upper pole of left kidney compatible with renal cyst; no hydronephrosis. Stomach and both small and large bowel loops normal caliber. No lymphadenopathy. Abdominal aorta normal caliber. No suspicious bone or soft tissue lesion identified.
MIXED BACTERIAL FLORA (>= 3 COLONY TYPES), CONSISTENT WITH SKIN AND/OR GENITAL CONTAMINATION.
